title: 10 most underreported humanitarian crises all in Africa for second year running, report finds
description: All 10 of the most underreported humanitarian crises of 2023 are in Africa, according to a new report by CARE International.

title: Who are the Houthi rebels and why are they attacking ships in the Red Sea?
description: Attacks by Yemen's Houthi rebels - both on Israel and on commercial ships in the Red Sea - have stoked fears of a wider conflict in the region, already affected by the war in Gaza.

title: Avalanche at California ski resort as snow and gusts hit west after deadly storms strike eastern US
description: Rescue teams are searching a California ski resort near Lake Tahoe following an avalanche - as a major storm with snow and gusty winds moved into the region.

title: Tory MPs attack 'draconian' ban on public bodies boycotting Israel
description: Rishi Sunak suffered a small rebellion on Wednesday night as eight Tory MPs voted against a "draconian" bill to ban public bodies from boycotting Israel.

title: 'Enough is enough': Western forces appear to be preparing strike on Houthi rebels after Red Sea attacks
description: British and US forces appear to be gearing up to strike an Iranian-backed militant group in Yemen after the Houthi rebels defied a warning to stop attacking ships in the Red Sea.

title: Boeing chief admits lapse in quality control after Alaska Airlines mid-air door blowout
description: The head of beleaguered plane maker Boeing has said "a quality escape" occurred in safety checks which led to a mid-flight blowout when a door 'plug' came off during a flight involving one of the jets made by the company.

title: Starbucks sued for allegedly using coffee from farms with abuses while touting ethical sourcing
description: Starbucks is being sued in the US for alleged false advertising over how ethically sourced its products are.

title: German far-right party denies backing deportation of 'unassimilated' citizens
description: Senior politicians from a German far-right party reportedly met neo-Nazi activists to discuss a proposal to deport "unassimilated" immigrants - even if they had citizenship.

title: Alexei Navalny jokes about Moscow 'naked party' in video call from Arctic penal colony
description: Jailed Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny cracked jokes about Moscow's "naked party" in his first court appearance since he was transferred to an Arctic penal colony.

title: 'It doesn't miss': British warship in Red Sea did 'exactly what it was designed for'
description: Seven drones launched by Iranian-backed Houthi fighters in the Red Sea have been shot down by a British warship which was "doing exactly the job" it was deployed for.

title: Brutal prison violence, a drug lord's escape and a nationwide curfew - what's happening in Ecuador?
description: The brazen spectacle of hooded gunmen bursting onto a live TV set - as chaos rules in the country's prisons - has once again thrown Ecuador's security crisis into the spotlight.

title: Norway becomes first country to back controversial deep sea mining
description: Controversial deep sea mining is one step closer to reality as Norway approved the practice in a parliamentary vote, sparking furious outcry from environmental campaigners.

title: Threats are in sharp focus on Taiwan's islands - where China's mainland is visible in the distance
description: There is a long queue of people waiting to board the ferry from the coastal city of Xiamen in southeast China.

title: 'Largest attack to date' in Red Sea repelled by HMS Diamond and US warships
description: A British warship and US forces have destroyed “multiple drones” launched by Iranian-backed Houthi fighters in the Red Sea, the British defence secretary has said.

title: 'Explosive' new attack drone developed by Iran for Russia's war in Ukraine
description: Iran has developed a new attack drone for Russia's war in Ukraine and appears close to providing Moscow with surface-to-surface missiles, an informed security source has claimed.
